typeDescription: Model information for a piece of scientific instrumentation used to perform experiments on the ECL.

fields.name: Name
fields.description: Name of this Object.

fields.name: ID
fields.description: ID of this Object.

fields.name: Object
fields.description: Object of this Object.

metadata.value: The object reference of this object.

fields.name: Type
fields.description: Type of this Object.

fields.name: Notebook
fields.description: Notebook this object belongs to.

fields.name: Objects
fields.description: Objects that represent instances of this model.

fields.name: Deprecated
fields.description: Indicates if this instrument model is historical and no longer used in the lab.

fields.name: Authors
fields.description: The person(s) who created this instrument model.

fields.name: ImageFile
fields.description: An example photo of this model of instrument.

fields.name: UserManualFiles
fields.description: PDFs for the manuals or instruction guides for this model of instrument.

fields.name: InstrumentSchematics
fields.description: Detailed drawings of the instrument that explain its capabilities and limitations.

fields.name: PowerType
fields.description: The type(s) of the power source(s) used by instruments of this model.

fields.name: BatteryRequirements
fields.description: All battery requirements for battery-powered instruments of this model.

fields.name: PowerConsumption
fields.description: Estimated power consumption rate of the instrument in Watts (Joule/Second).

fields.name: Connector
fields.description: All data connector requirements needed to interface the instruments of this model with a computer.

fields.name: OperatingSystem
fields.description: Operating system that the software of instruments of this model runs on.

fields.name: PCICard
fields.description: All PCICard requirements needed to install specialized hardware.

fields.name: Dongle
fields.description: Indicates if an instrument of this model requires a security dongle in the computer to run.

fields.name: AssociatedAccessories
fields.description: Items installed with the instrument for full function.

Item.value: Model[Instrument][SupportedInstruments] | Model[Part][SupportedInstruments] | Model[Container, PlateSealMagazine][SupportedInstruments] | Model[Container, MagazineParkPosition][SupportedInstruments] | Model[Sensor][SupportedInstruments] | Model[Item][SupportedInstruments] | Model[Plumbing][SupportedInstruments] | Model[Wiring][SupportedInstruments]

fields.name: WasteType
fields.description: The type of waste generated by this instrument.

fields.name: PricingRate
fields.description: The rate charged by the ECL for time used on this instrument in the course of conducting user experiments.

fields.name: PricingCategory
fields.description: The generic billing category this instrument model will be listed under.

fields.name: PricingLevel
fields.description: With respect to cost, the category of devices, for which this Instrument falls into.

fields.name: PlugRequirements
fields.description: All electrical requirements for plug-in parts of this model.

fields.name: AllowedPositions
fields.description: Generates a pattern of all the valid position names for this model of instrument.

fields.name: WettedMaterials
fields.description: A list of materials in the instrument which may be wetted by user-specified liquids.

fields.name: FacilityRequirementFiles
fields.description: PDFs for facility requirements and pre-installation checkoff forms provided by the supplier for instruments of this model.

fields.name: Dimensions
fields.description: The external dimensions of this model of instrument.

fields.name: CrossSectionalShape
fields.description: The shape of this model of instrument in the X-Y plane.

fields.name: ContainerImage2DFile
fields.description: A top-down (X-Y plane) image of this model of instrument which can be overlaid on a 2D container plot.

fields.name: Shape2D
fields.description: A Graphics primitive corresponding to the 2D shape of this model of instrument.

fields.name: Shape3D
fields.description: A Graphics primitive corresponding to the 3D shape of this model of instrument.

fields.name: Positions
fields.description: Spatial definitions of the positions that exist in this model of instrument.

fields.name: AvailableLayouts
fields.description: Readily available configurations of container models in specified positions on the deck of this instrument model.

fields.name: LocalCacheContents
fields.description: Items required to be present in the local cache for instruments of this model, along with the required quantity of each item.

fields.name: ProvidedStorageCondition
fields.description: The physical conditions such as temperature and humidity this instrument provides for samples stored long term within it.

fields.name: Connectors
fields.description: Specifications for the ports on this model of instrument that may connect to other plumbing components.

fields.name: WiringConnectors
fields.description: Specifications for the wiring ends of this instrument that may plug into and conductively connect to other items, parts or instruments.

fields.name: QualificationFrequency
fields.description: A list of the Qualifications which should be run on instruments of this model and their required frequencies.

fields.name: MaintenanceFrequency
fields.description: A list of the maintenance protocols which should be run on instruments of this model and their required frequencies.

fields.name: ReplacementParts
fields.description: A list of tracked replacement part models for this instrument.

fields.name: PassiveClean
fields.description: Indicates if the exterior surfaces of this instrument model can be cleaned while in use.

fields.name:
VentilationFlowRate
Requirement
fields.description: The minimum flow rate of air generated by the instrument's ventilator for its safe and proper function.

fields.name:
VentilationFlowRate
Recommendation
fields.description: The flow rate of air generated by the instrument's ventilator recommended by its manufacturer.

fields.name: ContinuousOperation
fields.description: Indicates if the instrument is required to operate continuously in the lab, regardless of if it is InUse by a specific protocol, such as a freezer.

fields.name: Manufacturer
fields.description: The company that originally manufactured this model of instrument.

fields.name: SupportedInstruments
fields.description: A list of instruments for which this model is an accompanying accessory.

fields.name: Sterile
fields.description: Indicates that this model of instrument is used for protocols where SterileTechnique is indicated to be used.

fields.name: CultureHandling
fields.description: Indicates the type of cellular samples (Mammalian or Microbial) that this instrument is used to handle.

fields.name: GloveBoxStorage
fields.description: Indiciates that this model of instrument permanently resides in the glove box.

fields.name: HazardCategories
fields.description: Hazards to be aware of during operation of instruments of this model.

fields.name: SampleHandlingCategories
fields.description: Special handling considerations that samples on this instrument require.

fields.name: SensorBarrier
fields.description: Type of sensors which cannot monitor the internal contents of instruments of this model from the outside.
